{
  "texts": [
    "These transitions may suggest that both interventions were influential in encouraging students to move beyond superficial use of AI and to engage in a more iterative and thoughtful coding process, as supported by studies recommending that guidance for AI literacy and prompt writing can enhance the educational use of AI tools (Silva et al., 2024; Yilmaz & Yilmaz, 2023b; Yu, 2023).",
    "The significant growth in the AI-collaborative profile in third session, where students used ChatGPT to seek specific guidance and integrate it into their problemsolving process, may be the impact of guidance document on sample prompts.",
    "This finding supports the notion that instructional interventions can transform AI from a passive source of answers into an active learning partner (Weng et al., 2024).",
    "The drop in using AI assistance for code refinement may suggest that as students gained confidence and skill in interacting with ChatGPT, they moved towards more collaborative interactions, rather than utilizing AI for refining code.",
    "This shift is consistent with literature emphasizing the importance of developing students' AI literacy and critical thinking skills (Yilmaz & Yilmaz, 2023b)."
  ]
}